The TETRA fork adds:
- Bearer-token middleware on HTTP transports (src/middleware/auth.py)
- /health route registered on the streamable-HTTP transport
- OAuth2 client_credentials grant (in addition to upstream's password grant)
- Configurable URL prefix (KEYCLOAK_BASE_PATH) for KC v17+ deployments
- Pydantic-settings configuration with SecretStr handling
- StandaloneSseWriterRaceFilter logging filter
- Dockerfile aligned with TETRA scaffold (Python 3.12, non-root, healthcheck)
- Registers authentication_management_tools (upstream omitted from __init__.py)
